 are in butterfly form.<\/p>\n\n<p>So if we are talking about the butterflies' heart, we can say that some species' heart are younger than their real age, while others are older than their real age. What is the name of this phenomenon?<\/p>\n","question_id":39891,"tags":["terminology","senescence"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":45,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1445733236},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f5384ef0aa4badda1f41daf83aca68bb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":17488,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/17488/mpg","reputation":38,"display_name":"MPG","accept_rate":25},"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39915/pando-clonal-colony","last_activity_date":1445730329,"creation_date":1445730329,"answer_count":0,"title":"Pando clonal colony","body":"<p>What is the specificity of the Pando clonal colony? Can it be implemented on other plants? What aired the basic mechanisms that support the growth and sustenance of this clonal colony?<\/p>\n","question_id":39915,"tags":["plant-anatomy"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":16,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2186bd6edc2730b4ef1b3ee0060235fb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16417,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16417/mirin","reputation":17,"display_name":"mirin"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f94e67a8de70fccd254ef725a3e494a8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16147,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16147/inactionpotential","reputation":519,"display_name":"InactionPotential"},"score":4,"post_id":35547,"edited":false,"creation_date":1435349882,"comment_id":58046,"body":"It would be helpful if you could provide an actual excerpt from the text instead of a garbled summation. It&#39;s honestly hard to tell what 