 a try in a worst case?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":1,"post_id":39363,"edited":false,"creation_date":1444225429,"comment_id":65886,"body":"Because HIV can be controlled for quite a while with the actual medication. And who will be the person conducting these experiments? This is unethical."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"score":1,"post_id":39363,"edited":false,"creation_date":1444241057,"comment_id":65899,"body":"The reason AIDS develops is that your normal run of the mill immune cells are plenty potent enough to kill off all of your Helper T-Cells that are infected with HIV, so now you want to let loose killers that are not necessarily specific to cells infected with HIV that will lay waste to everything else?"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":4,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/100002720296550/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":15907,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15907/johny-royan","reputation":33,"display_name":"Johny Royan"},"score":0,"post_id":39364,"edited":false,"creation_date":1444226009,"comment_id":65887,"body":"Then why not try the vice versa: treating Leukemia with HIV?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.co