 meant <strong>closely related species<\/strong>, or did he have individual organisms in mind? <\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>DETECTION OF HORIZONTAL GENE TRANSFER <\/p>\n  \n  <p>There are several approaches to identify genetic changes due to HGT,\n  including:  <\/p>\n  \n  <p>(1) experimental evidence, whereby a genetic marker is monitored for\n  gene transfer to a recipient organism;  <\/p>\n  \n  <p>(2) phylogenetic analysisof gene sequences to identify topological\n  inconsistencies between different gene families;   <\/p>\n  \n  <p>(3) nucleotide compositional analysis to identify any gene that has a\n  nucleotide pattern that differs significantly from the overall genome;\n  and   <\/p>\n  \n  <p>(4) evolutionary scenarios to explain the patchy appearance of a\n  genetic signature, sequence or function that is not shared by <strong>close<\/strong>\n  <strong>relatives<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>(From \"<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18801324\" rel=\"nofollow\">Risks from GMOs due to Horizontal Gene Transfer<\/a>\", by Paul Keese)<\/p>\n","question_id":38699,"tags":["genetics","genomics","horizontal-gene-transfer"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":39805,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":31,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1442073063},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5a061a72feb5b6580dadd5dcbc92d3b5?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6918,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6918/tom%c3%a1%c5%a1-zato","reputation":325,"display_name":"Tomáš Zato","accept_rate":57},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/KD6Fx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3952,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3952/oreotrephes","reputation":4267,"display_name":"Oreotrephes","accept_rate":86},"score":0,"post_id":21295,"edited":false,"creation_date":1410710174,"comment_id":33445,"body":"Here&#39;s a null hypothesis based on perception bias: 