se we can dispose it."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1a7c88f358cea3842961d9c4bb16b2d6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19440,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19440/chris-cook","reputation":25,"display_name":"Chris Cook"},"score":0,"post_id":39762,"edited":false,"creation_date":1445286783,"comment_id":66681,"body":"thanks guys! this helps alot"}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39762/mutations-induced-by-transposons","last_activity_date":1445339198,"creation_date":1445243034,"answer_count":0,"title":"mutations induced by transposons","body":"<p>Question:<\/p>\n\n<p>In contrast to chemically-induced mutations, mutations induced by transposons are more likely to ...<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>be lethal<\/li>\n<li>de dominant<\/li>\n<li>be stable<\/li>\n<li>revert to wild types<\/li>\n<li>be a gain of function<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>The answer is 4; but I have no understanding of why this is the correct answer, or, why the others answers are not correct.  Could someone help to explain why this is the case?<\/p>\n","question_id":39762,"tags":["genetics","molecular-biology","homework","molecular-genetics"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":91,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1445339198},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/75cd6628bae4bfced46f3d3c755f537d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9757,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9757/user50746","reputation":113,"display_name":"user50746"},"closed_date":1436848672,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":3,"post_id":36029,"edited":false,"creation_date":1436758147,"comment_id":59451,"body":"The thing that comes out of the banana in the video i