cies. Some suffered natural extinctions, while others were exterminated by humans. Still others may have been on their way out when humans along and finished them off.<\/p>\n\n<p>But I'd like to get a general grasp of what happened. It seems that giant ground sloths would have been easily exterminated by human hunters, just as the smaller ground sloths of the Caribbean islands disappeared after the islands were settled by humans. The pony-sized mammoths that inhabited various islands off the coast of California and Europe also seem like good candidates for human extermination.<\/p>\n","question_id":39753,"tags":["extinction"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":25,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ac86876355c1b946c74b52425aaa8557?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14994,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14994/jake-soleri","reputation":27,"display_name":"Jake Soleri"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1b3c5b025ca581db5a8fdd2564b5367c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6511,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6511/bez","reputation":2430,"display_name":"Bez"},"score":4,"post_id":30542,"edited":false,"creation_date":1426706749,"comment_id":50518,"body":"possible duplication of <a href=\"http://skeptics.stackexchange.com/questions/2948/does-brain-mass-have-any-correlation-to-intelligence\" title=\"does brain mass have any correlation to intelligence\">skeptics.stackexchange.com/questions/2948/&hellip;<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/v5upF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3624,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3624/fileunderwater","reputation":10502,"display_name":"fileunderwater"},"score":0,"post_id":30542,"edited":false,"creation_date":1426774208,"comment_id":50591,"body":"related: <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/ques